This product builds on architectural patterns and depends on the following
upstream projects (consumed via lockfile-pinned dependencies — wrap-don't-fork
per ADR 0001):

  agent-dag-pipeline
  https://github.com/Manzela/agent-dag-pipeline
  Apache License 2.0
  Author: Daniel Manzela
  Provides: Gate-Agent ABC pattern, DEMAS Provenance Matrix, 3-tier DPO
  flywheel, Hebbian prompt mutator, ADK integration wrappers (gate_agent,
  pipeline, runner, callbacks, eval, guardrails, tools, agent_card, deploy).
  Atelier consumes via `pip install agent-dag-pipeline==<pinned>` and
  subclasses public APIs without modifying upstream source.

  hermes-agent
  https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent
  MIT License
  Author: Nous Research
  Inspired: skills system, MEMORY/SOUL files, sandboxing tier model,
  panic/resume primitives, Atropos GRPO+LoRA training pattern, two-prompt
  harness adoption. Atelier mirrors patterns; does NOT run hermes-agent
  as a process or import its code directly.

  google-adk
  https://github.com/google/adk-python
  Apache License 2.0
  Author: Google LLC
  Provides: SequentialAgent, ParallelAgent, LoopAgent, MCPToolset,
  rubric_based_*_v1 evaluators, Skills for Agents, adk optimize (GEPA),
  adk conformance, adk eval CLI. Atelier consumes via
  `pip install google-adk --pre` lockfile-pinned.

  Stitch MCP
  https://stitch.googleapis.com/mcp
  Google Labs / DeepMind product
  Atelier consumes via ADK's `MCPToolset` HTTP client — no source dependency.

  Anthropic two-prompt harness pattern
  https://github.com/anthropics/claude-quickstarts/tree/main/autonomous-coding
  Apache License 2.0
  Author: Anthropic, PBC
  Pattern adopted for the build sprint discipline (initializer + coding
  agent + JSON ledger + end-to-end test before next feature).

